%% Phase: 6
%% Status: verified
%% Source evidence: frontend/src/services/api.ts; frontend/src/types/api.ts; backend/src/routes; backend/src/error.rs
%% Related documentation: ../frontend-contract-map.md; ../request-contracts.md; ../response-contracts.md
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Feature as React Feature
    participant Types as TypeScript Contract
    participant Client as Shared API Client
    participant Router as Axum Route
    participant DTO as Rust DTO and Handler

    Feature->>Types: Construct typed request or expected response
    Feature->>Client: Call domain API method
    Client->>Client: Resolve base URL and JSON headers
    opt Authenticated call
        Client->>Client: Add bearer and selected organization headers
    end
    Client->>Router: HTTP method and path
    Router->>DTO: Extract, deserialize, validate, and authorize
    alt Success
        DTO-->>Client: JSON response
        Client-->>Feature: Parsed generic type T
    else Failure
        DTO-->>Client: ErrorBody or non-uniform transport failure
        Client-->>Feature: ApiError with status and message
    end
    Note over Types,DTO: TypeScript contracts are manually duplicated from Rust; no generated parity check exists
